   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "13e80e77-375f-4e6c-a85d-7441364c6685",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Business Understanding\n",
    "\n",
    "In this project we will predict whether a machine will fail based on operational data. This is a supervised learning binary classification problem where:\n",
    "- 0 = No failure\n",
    "- 1 = Failure\n",
    "  \n",
    "The goal is to support predictive maintenance strategies by identifying machines likely to fail before they actually do. Given that undetected failures can lead to unplanned downtime and higher maintenance costs, recall will be one of the most important metrics. However, precision will also be considered to avoid alarm fatigue in the maintenance team."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "8cf0f086-ae23-4574-8ee7-d74209187ba3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
