  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1c89abb6-f101-4aaf-9191-50f0dfc5d502",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Air temperature follows a relative symmetric distribution centered around 300°K, with no outliers detected in the boxplot. The limited variability suggest that temperature remain stable during the process and does not appear to be a strong indicator of machine failure.\n",
    "- Process temperature follows a relative symmetric distribution centered around 310°K, with no outliers. The absense of extreme values suggests stable operation conditions. This variable may have limited predictive power when used independently.\n",
    "- Rotational speed presents a wider distribution compared to temperature variables and contains several outliers identified in the boxplot. A scatter plot is needed to see if they fall under a realistic operation or they are errors.\n",
    "- Torque shows a broader spread and contains multiple outliers identified in the boxplot, this outliers shall be investigated to see if they are real operating values or error in measurements.\n",
    "- Tool wear shows variability across observations with no outliers, this variable may be related with machine failures since increased wear time, leads to operational failures."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "8cb7cee0-ce65-4e8e-9768-ba1ffe5bb86c",
