   "source": [
    "## Final Model: Random Forest with Adjusted Threshold\n",
    "\n",
    "Although this model has a lower recall compared to Logistic Regression, it is compensated by its precision. Out of all the real failures in the test set, the model detected 56 of them and of those 56 alerts, 95% were actual failures, meaning only 3 were false alarms.  \n",
    "  \n",
    "The other model was discarded precisely because of their low precision. A model that generates too many false alarms can lead the maintenance team to develop what is known as alarm fatigue, where technicians start assuming that most alerts are not real, and stop treating them with the urgency they deserve. And when an actual failure occurs, the team may not respond in time.\n",
    "  \n",
    "So by keeping precision at 95% and recall at 82%, the system stays credible and useful in a real industrial environment."
   ]
